import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt


img = cv2.imread("../data/leaf.png") # gray scale , 1    .
gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

img2 = cv2.imread("../data/hough_example.jpg") # gray scale , 1    .
gray2 = cv2.cvtColor(img2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)


gray = np.float32(gray)
dst = cv2.cornerHarris(gray,3,3,0.04) #C   

gray2 = np.float32(gray2)
dst2 = cv2.cornerHarris(gray2,3,3,0.04) #C   


#img[dst>0.01*dst.max()] = [0,0,255] #  .

print(" :  ",np.sum(dst>0.01*dst.max()))
coord_y=np.where(dst>0.07*dst.max())[0]
coord_x=np.where(dst>0.07*dst.max())[1]
for x,y in zip(coord_x,coord_y):
    cv2.circle(img,(x,y), 2,(0,0,255) ,-1 ) #    (c 0.07*  )




print("  :  ",np.sum(dst2>0.01*dst2.max()))
coord_y=np.where(dst2>0.01*dst2.max())[0]
coord_x=np.where(dst2>0.01*dst2.max())[1]
for x,y in zip(coord_x,coord_y):
    cv2.circle(img2,(x,y), 2,(0,255,0) ,-1 ) #    (c 0.01*  )
#img[img==[0,0,0]] = [255,0,0]

img= cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 
img2= cv2.cvtColor(img2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 

fig =plt.figure(figsize=(13,13))

plt.imshow(img)

# ex) harris corner and localization
#     .
import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

count=0
count2=0

img = cv2.imread("../data/leaf.png") # gray scale , 1    .
gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

img2 = cv2.imread("../data/hough_example.jpg") # gray scale , 1    .
gray2 = cv2.cvtColor(img2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)


gray = np.float32(gray)
dst = cv2.cornerHarris(gray,3,3,0.04) #C   

gray2 = np.float32(gray2)
dst2 = cv2.cornerHarris(gray2,3,3,0.04) #C   



# 
for y in range(dst.shape[0]-1):
    for x in range(dst.shape[1]-1):
        temp = dst[y,x]
        if temp>0.07*dst.max() and (temp > dst[y,x-1]) and (temp>dst[y,x+1]) and (temp>dst[y-1,x]) and (temp>dst[y+1,x]):
            count=count+1
            cv2.circle(img,(x,y), 2,(0,0,255) ,-1 )
            #img[y,x]=[0,255,0]

print("   : ", count)
img_rgb= cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 


# 
for y in range(1,dst2.shape[0]-1):
    for x in range(1,dst2.shape[1]-1):
        temp = dst2[y,x]
        if temp>0.01*dst2.max() and (temp > dst2[y,x-1]) and (temp>dst2[y,x+1]) and (temp>dst2[y-1,x]) and (temp>dst2[y+1,x]):
            count2=count2+1
            cv2.circle(img2,(x,y), 2,(0,255,0) ,-1 )
            #img[y,x]=[0,255,0]

print("    : ", count2)
img_rgb2= cv2.cvtColor(img2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 





fig =plt.figure(figsize=(13,13))

plt.subplot(221)# 2 2 1
plt.imshow(img_rgb)

plt.subplot(222)# 2 2 2
plt.imshow(img_rgb2)


plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt


img = cv2.imread("../data/face_model.jpg")
gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

img2 = cv2.imread("../data/face_model_small.jpg")
gray2 = cv2.cvtColor(img2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)


#SIFT  
sift = cv2.xfeatures2d.SIFT_create() #default

#keypoint 
keypoints,descriptor = sift.detectAndCompute(gray, None)
print(" keypoint  : ", len(keypoints))

keypoints2,descriptor2 = sift.detectAndCompute(gray2, None)
print("1/2  keypoint  : ", len(keypoints2))

# 
img_draw = cv2.drawKeypoints(img, keypoints, None,flags=cv2.DRAW_MATCHES_FLAGS_DEFAULT)
img_draw2 = cv2.drawKeypoints(img2, keypoints2, None,flags=cv2.DRAW_MATCHES_FLAGS_DEFAULT)



# cv2.DRAW_MATCHES_FLAGS_DEFAULT :      

img_rgb= cv2.cvtColor(img_draw, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 
img_rgb2= cv2.cvtColor(img_draw2, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)#PLOT 

fig =plt.figure(figsize=(13,13))

plt.subplot(221),plt.title(" ")# 2 2 1
plt.imshow(img_rgb)

plt.subplot(222),plt.title("1/2 ")# 2 2 1
plt.imshow(img_rgb2)
